(fetchWidth, area_cell_area).explanation: Increasing fetch width requires wider instruction fetch units and larger multiplexers, directly increasing the physical area occupied by cells in the processor design;

(fetchWidth, power_register).explanation: Wider fetch width necessitates more registers to store the additional fetched instructions, directly increasing register file power consumption;

(fetchWidth, nL2TLBEntries).explanation: Fetch width determines instruction fetch rate while L2 TLB entries are determined by memory management requirements and are independent architectural decisions;
